dataElements.name: CH_PR_16_DISEASE-PHASE
dataElements.description:
Disease phase:

Acute: acute phase of the disease with T. cruzi detection in direct microscopic observation of blood.  

Chronic: chronic phase of the disease (without direct evidence of T. cruzi presence in blood and
diagnosis done with indirect lab tests, such as serological test).

Reactivation: Reactivation by immunodepression of a chronic case with T. cruzi detection in direct microscopic observation of blood.
